87
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:36,780
I think you should tell him.

88
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:39,120
Forget it.

89
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:44,000
If he doesn't like me, he'll just make fun of me.

90
00:05:48,266 --> 00:05:51,603
If he doesn't make fun of you after he knows it,

91
00:05:51,603 --> 00:05:53,346
he might love you.

92
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:56,440
Will you regret it if you don't do it?

93
00:06:00,060 --> 00:06:04,320
I think people's feelings can change.

94
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:06,780
Just because he has no feelings for you

95
00:06:06,780 --> 00:06:09,560
doesn't mean you have to give up.

96
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,860
As long as he doesn't have a girlfriend,

97
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:17,340
you still have a chance to make him fall in love with you.

98
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:33,138
Whether you want to confess your feelings to him or not,

99
00:06:33,660 --> 00:06:35,700
it depends on you.

100
00:06:35,700 --> 00:06:38,020
But I want to ask you something.

101
00:06:38,465 --> 00:06:40,520
Don't do anything that goes against your heart.

102
00:06:40,520 --> 00:06:42,800
I'm not.

103
00:06:42,800 --> 00:06:45,580
You asked Kirin out.

104
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:49,620
He doesn't feel that way about me.

105
00:06:49,620 --> 00:06:51,700
We're friends.

106
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:56,052
But people's feelings can change, Khun Ross.

107
00:06:56,052 --> 00:06:57,400
Maybe he doesn't love you right now,

108
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,400
but what if he falls in love with you later?

109
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:01,380
Khun Kirin is your friend.

110
00:07:01,380 --> 00:07:06,840
If he knows that you're messing with him,

111
00:07:06,840 --> 00:07:08,860
how sad would he be?

112
00:07:08,860 --> 00:07:11,790
It's very painful

113
00:07:11,790 --> 00:07:16,070
to be cheated and betrayed...

114
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:18,920
by someone you trust.

115
00:07:27,240 --> 00:07:30,840
When you are unhappy and don't want to say anything,

116
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:33,180
vent it out by painting.

117
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:36,600
It will put you in a better mood.

118
00:07:42,319 --> 00:07:43,960
Doctor.

119
00:07:45,599 --> 00:07:49,380
If someone made you fall in love with her,

120
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:54,000
but you found out that she lied to you, what would you do?

121
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:56,680
In that case, I would be very upset.

122
00:07:56,680 --> 00:08:00,620
I would cut her off.

123
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,720
Why did you ask me that?

124
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:05,760
Who are you tricking to fall in love with you?

125
00:08:08,146 --> 00:08:10,020
You don't answer me.

126
00:08:10,020 --> 00:08:11,260
Let me put it another way.

127
00:08:11,260 --> 00:08:14,420
You said you were tricking someone to fall in love with you.

128
00:08:14,420 --> 00:08:19,040
Do you mean you're tricking her to fall in love with you,

129
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:22,240
or are you tricking yourself?

130
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:25,740
You thought you didn't love her, but you're dating her.

131
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:29,320
You can't answer.

132
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:30,760
Let me get this straight.

133
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:36,240
The person you're tricking is Khun Kheetika. Right?

134
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:38,520
Doctor.

135
00:08:39,160 --> 00:08:41,440
How did you know it was Kheetika?

136
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:46,560
Your recent questions are all about Khun Kheetika.

137
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,760
Why are you tricking her?

138
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:51,960
Why don't you admit how you feel?

139
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:54,020
Is it that difficult?

140
00:08:54,020 --> 00:08:56,960
If it were that simple, would I still come to you for advice?

141
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:59,860
Are you blaming me?

142
00:08:59,860 --> 00:09:01,140
Yes.

143
00:09:01,140 --> 00:09:02,640
Hey, I remembered a word.

144
00:09:02,640 --> 00:09:05,720
It's often said that where there is love, there is pain.

145
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:08,520
See, I'm in pain.

146
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:10,800
I really don't understand.

147
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:14,520
Just paint. Just vent it out.

148
00:09:26,959 --> 00:09:28,500
You.

149
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:35,920
Are you hungry? Do you want me to prepare your meal?

150
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:38,360
I'm still full.

151
00:09:46,880 --> 00:09:50,840
I must make it clear today. What is going on with him?

152
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:52,973
Is he suffering from manic depression?

153
00:09:57,660 --> 00:10:00,860
It's 11:00 p.m., but he hasn't come home yet.

154
00:10:00,860 --> 00:10:03,460
Did something happen to him?

155
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:07,080
Khun Sira, where are you?

156
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:09,800
Dr. Zhao.

157
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:16,240
You can't solve the problem by hiding like this, Khun Sira.

158
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,520
It's the only way I can think of.

159
00:10:18,520 --> 00:10:21,680
How long are you going to hide?

160
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:32,360
Khun Sira.

161
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,260
What are you doing here?

162
00:10:37,260 --> 00:10:41,120
You came to Dr. Zhao's house. Are you sick?

163
00:10:41,120 --> 00:10:44,560
I am not sick. I'm all right.

164
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:48,600
You're staying with the doctor, and you don't want to go home.

165
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,600
You call it normal?

166
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:54,260
What's the matter with you these days? It looks like you're avoiding me.

167
00:10:54,260 --> 00:10:56,040
Are you angry with me?

168
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:58,840
You can tell me.

169
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:00,720
I'm not angry at you.

170
00:11:00,720 --> 00:11:03,060
I just want to be alone.

171
00:11:03,060 --> 00:11:06,740
You don't have to take care of me this time around.

172
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:11,020
Am I bothering you?

173
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:13,740
No.

174
00:11:13,740 --> 00:11:17,160
I just like to be alone and think alone.

175
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:20,340
You can go back. I think I'll spend the night at Dr. Zhao's.

176
00:11:20,340 --> 00:11:23,040
Oh, you're going to spend the night here?

177
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:24,560
Yes.

178
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:26,960
I'm sorry for causing you trouble.

179
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:41,240
- What?
- Don't turn around.

180
00:11:41,240 --> 00:11:43,080
I have something to tell you.

181
00:11:43,080 --> 00:11:45,580
But I don't dare say it to your face.

182
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:49,500
I used to like being alone.

183
00:11:49,500 --> 00:11:53,320
I thought I was going to cause trouble for others.

184
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:55,500
But since you've come into my life,

185
00:11:56,080 --> 00:12:00,850
I've learned that it's good...

186
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:03,560
