244
00:15:52,260 --> 00:15:57,260
But they spend less on average than customers aged 20 to 30.

245
00:15:57,260 --> 00:15:59,520
It's just a report.

246
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:02,140
Everything can change.

247
00:16:03,040 --> 00:16:06,400
But I think we should believe the surveyed reports.

248
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:10,960
Because it's better than taking a risk of doing something without any information.

249
00:16:13,280 --> 00:16:18,880
Besides the survey that was done, what else does your sales group have in mind?

250
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:21,400
Nothing else.

251
00:16:24,740 --> 00:16:27,200
Khun Pa. Khun Kirin.

252
00:16:27,200 --> 00:16:30,160
Do you have anything to say?

253
00:16:30,160 --> 00:16:33,700
Khun Pa and I thought of another idea. We think...

254
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:35,060
But your plan isn't perfect.

255
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:37,677
So I don't want you to say it. It's a waste of time.

256
00:16:37,677 --> 00:16:39,566
It's not a waste of time.

257
00:16:39,566 --> 00:16:41,491
We still have a lot of time.

258
00:16:41,491 --> 00:16:45,339
Maybe we'll have new ideas.

259
00:16:45,339 --> 00:16:46,200
Go ahead.

260
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:49,000
Excuse me, Khun Kheetika.

261
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,960
You are not the head of the Design Department.

262
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:55,800
It's up to me whether I want them to talk or not.

263
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:59,480
Do I have the right to decide

264
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:01,760
as the grandson of the chairman of GU?

265
00:17:05,120 --> 00:17:07,540
We still have half an hour.

266
00:17:07,540 --> 00:17:10,820
Khun Palida and Khun Kirin, if you have any plans, please present them to us.

267
00:17:10,820 --> 00:17:12,860
Is that okay?

268
00:17:12,860 --> 00:17:14,360
Thank you.

269
00:17:14,360 --> 00:17:19,960
We want to target customers aged 20 to 30.

270
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:23,580
So, about the clothes, we want...

271
00:17:23,580 --> 00:17:26,080
Khun Kheetika.

272
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:31,260
Thank you so much for giving us the opportunity to talk about our plan.

273
00:17:31,260 --> 00:17:32,750
That's right.

274
00:17:32,750 --> 00:17:35,600
You worked hard.

275
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:37,540
It would be a shame if you couldn't talk about your plan.

276
00:17:37,540 --> 00:17:39,940
I'm so happy.

277
00:17:39,940 --> 00:17:43,260
Khun Kansinee doesn't like to listen to our proposals.

278
00:17:43,260 --> 00:17:47,080
She rejects our ideas directly and focuses on her own ideas.

279
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:48,399
It's true.

280
00:17:48,399 --> 00:17:53,220
I really want you to come back and be our supervisor.

281
00:17:53,220 --> 00:17:57,160
Can you come back to us?

282
00:17:57,160 --> 00:17:59,205
I don't think she can.

283
00:18:02,760 --> 00:18:05,260
As long as I'm working here,

284
00:18:05,260 --> 00:18:09,020
there can only be one head of the Design Department.

285
00:18:12,180 --> 00:18:17,740
Then please do your part as a leader.

286
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:20,600
Because it's all about teamwork.

287
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:24,160
It's not about you.

288
00:18:25,740 --> 00:18:27,660
How I work is my own business.

289
00:18:27,660 --> 00:18:31,500
Those who can do it, endure it; those who can't, resign.

290
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:41,480
Do you think you can do whatever you want with the chairwoman backing you?

291
00:18:41,480 --> 00:18:43,100
That's right.

292
00:18:44,040 --> 00:18:47,900
You should also be careful.

293
00:18:47,900 --> 00:18:50,870
Don't think because Khun Sasa and Khun Sira are backing you,

294
00:18:50,870 --> 00:18:53,820
I can't deal with you.

295
00:18:56,180 --> 00:19:00,760
We'll see whether you will kick me out

296
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:04,080
or I will kick the chairwoman's people

297
00:19:04,080 --> 00:19:07,960
out for a second time.

298
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:21,990
Madam, I wish you

299
00:19:21,990 --> 00:19:26,360
good health and a long life.

300
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:28,740
Amitabha.

301
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:32,420
Time flies.

302
00:19:32,420 --> 00:19:34,860
It's been over 20 years.

303
00:19:34,860 --> 00:19:38,060
Your grandchildren have all grown up, haven't they?

304
00:19:38,060 --> 00:19:40,900
They can help with your company.

305
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:43,240
Yes, Master.

306
00:19:43,240 --> 00:19:45,620
I'm also exhausted.

307
00:19:45,620 --> 00:19:50,440
I want to hand over the company to them.

308
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:55,300
Your two deceased sons should be relieved

309
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:59,620
to see their sons managing the company.

310
00:19:59,620 --> 00:20:04,550
I hope you will let go of the past

311
00:20:04,550 --> 00:20:07,460
in your later years.

312
00:20:07,460 --> 00:20:13,220
Don't let the sins of the dead be shackles on the living.

313
00:20:13,220 --> 00:20:15,860
You won't be happy that way.

314
00:20:21,620 --> 00:20:25,140
If you choose to be with that woman, don't come back home.

315
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:27,000
Madam.

316
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:30,000
You will leave with nothing.

317
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,560
You can't get a baht from me.

318
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:36,651
I'd like to know if you have nothing,

319
00:20:36,651 --> 00:20:40,440
whether that greedy woman will still love you.

320
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:45,726
Mom, don't worry.

321
00:20:45,726 --> 00:20:48,860
All I want is not your money.

322
00:20:48,860 --> 00:20:51,060
I just want a free life.

323
00:20:51,060 --> 00:20:53,260
I want to choose what I want.

324
00:20:53,260 --> 00:20:55,900
I want to work hard to get what I like.

325
00:20:55,900 --> 00:20:57,800
That's all I want.

326
00:20:57,800 --> 00:21:00,200
It's your decision.

327
00:21:13,640 --> 00:21:17,140
Burn everything and all the pictures.

328
00:21:17,140 --> 00:21:21,500
I won't allow this unfilial son to stay in my house.

329
00:21:22,700 --> 00:21:26,780
Tell everyone not to mention his name again.

330
00:22:11,540 --> 00:22:16,400
Khun Kheetika, do you have anything to do after work today?

331
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:19,840
No. What's the matter?

332
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:23,940
I want to invite you to the back of the mall to eat Som Tum (papaya salad).

333
00:22:23,940 --> 00:22:26,440
I want to thank you for that day.

334
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:28,640
It's all right, you don't have to invite me to dinner.

335
00:22:28,640 --> 00:22:32,440
Who's buying dinner? Can I come with you?

336
00:22:32,440 --> 00:22:36,740
All right. We're going to eat Som Tum.

337
00:22:36,740 --> 00:22:38,380
Do you want to come with us?

338
00:22:38,380 --> 00:22:40,720
Okay. I'm hungry.

339
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:44,200
Why don't I treat you?

340
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:45,600
Why do you want to treat me?

341
00:22:45,600 --> 00:22:47,600
I want to apologize to you.

342
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:52,940
Khun Rossarin, I'm sorry for going too far with my words,

343
00:22:52,940 --> 00:22:57,380
and for being mean to you lately.

344
00:22:57,380 --> 00:22:59,560
Please don't be angry at me.

345
00:22:59,560 --> 00:23:01,560
Let's make it up.

346
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:12,040
I swear I won't say anything to make you sad again.

347
00:23:12,040 --> 00:23:13,880
I swear.

348
00:23:20,940 --> 00:23:26,940
Brother, do you think Grandma asked us to dinner today to complain to us?

349
00:23:26,940 --> 00:23:28,840
You think too much, Din.

350
00:23:28,840 --> 00:23:35,340
Maybe the chairwoman just wants to have dinner with us.

351
00:23:35,340 --> 00:23:39,160
We've been busy lately.

352
00:23:39,160 --> 00:23:41,270
We didn't spend time with her.

353
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:45,960
Don't you remember? Grandma used to call us to dinner

354
00:23:45,960 --> 00:23:48,300
because she must have something to scold us about.

355
00:23:48,300 --> 00:23:51,240
She scolded us for more than an hour at a time.

356
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:55,840
How about this, Brother? Let's tell Grandma we have a meeting, and we can't go there.

357
00:23:55,840 --> 00:24:00,020
Din, how about this? I think you should find some time to spend with Grandma.

358
00:24:00,020 --> 00:24:02,240
She only has the two of us.

359
00:24:04,752 --> 00:24:09,460
And you're her only grandson.

360
00:24:11,152 --> 00:24:14,100
I'm not Grandma's only grandson.

361
00:24:14,100 --> 00:24:16,880
You're Grandma's grandson, too.

362
00:24:18,440 --> 00:24:21,485
Khun Sira. Din.

363
00:24:22,472 --> 00:24:25,139
- What is it?
- Maha and Khun Rossarin have reconciled.

364
00:24:25,139 --> 00:24:29,400
- Really?
- Yes. Just now, Maha apologized to Rossarin.

365
00:24:29,406 --> 00:24:33,360
Now they're going to the back of the mall to eat Som Tum.

366
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:36,400
But why did Maha suddenly apologize to Khun Rossarin?

367
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:40,060
- Did something happen that we don't know about?
- Maybe...

368
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:44,120
Maha figured it out himself.

369
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:48,360
Maha is smart. He realized that he was too mean to joke about Khun Rossarin

370
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:51,760
and that Khun Rossarin was his friend. Maybe he doesn't want to lose a friend.

371
00:24:51,760 --> 00:24:55,860
Since Maha and Khun Rossarin have reconciled, it means I did it.

372
00:24:55,860 --> 00:24:58,360
You should deliver on your promise.

373
00:25:09,126 --> 00:25:13,773
Din, I think you could ask her out another day.

374
00:25:13,773 --> 00:25:15,760
It's too late.

375
00:25:15,760 --> 00:25:19,760
I've already sent a message to Grandma. I told her I couldn't have dinner with her today.

376
00:25:19,760 --> 00:25:21,860
It's only you who's going.

377
00:25:23,312 --> 00:25:26,780
- Din.
- Brother, don't be mad at me.

378
00:25:26,780 --> 00:25:30,560
I live with Grandmother. I can eat with her any day.

379
00:25:30,560 --> 00:25:33,820
But it's difficult to eat with Kanghan.

380
00:25:33,820 --> 00:25:36,660
I won't miss this opportunity.

381
00:25:37,660 --> 00:25:40,320
You had a deal. She will agree to eat with you.

382
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:42,480
Ask her out another day.

383
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:44,300
I want to do it today.

384
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:46,220
I'll have another chance another day, Brother.

385
00:25:46,220 --> 00:25:52,040
Please accompany Grandma to dinner today. Okay?

386
00:25:54,380 --> 00:25:59,240
Didn't you promise to help me pursue Kanghan?

387
00:26:01,780 --> 00:26:04,251
Come on, the two of them are waiting for us.

388
00:26:04,251 --> 00:26:06,240
Let's go.

389
00:26:06,300 --> 00:26:10,440
I messaged Khun Rossarin that we weren't going.

390
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:13,080
Why not? I promised them.

391
00:26:13,080 --> 00:26:19,260
I want them to be alone. So they can talk about themselves.

392
00:26:19,260 --> 00:26:23,520
As for us, we'll go somewhere else to eat.

393
00:26:26,172 --> 00:26:32,360
If you're photographed eating alone and it's sent to the chairman, you will have a problem.

394
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:34,080
Go another time. I'll go with you.

395
00:26:34,080 --> 00:26:35,980
The chairwoman doesn't look busy.

396
00:26:35,980 --> 00:26:37,880
She always has time to pick on me.

397
00:26:37,880 --> 00:26:41,980
Hey, you. Please respect the chairwoman when you talk.

398
00:26:41,980 --> 00:26:44,960
Why should I respect her? Did she ever think about respecting me?

399
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:47,740
She always thinks I want to pester her grandson.

400
00:26:47,740 --> 00:26:53,100
I wonder what the chairwoman would do

401
00:26:53,100 --> 00:26:55,480
if I went to dinner alone with Din.

402
00:26:56,427 --> 00:26:58,427
Let's go, Din.

403
00:27:01,100 --> 00:27:02,980
Let's go.

404
00:27:10,546 --> 00:27:13,326
No need to set the table.

405
00:27:13,326 --> 00:27:16,780
Are you going out to dinner with Khun Din and Khun Lom today?

406
00:27:16,780 --> 00:27:21,160
No. Din is busy, he can't come to dinner with me.

407
00:27:21,160 --> 00:27:24,060
Call Lom and tell him not to come.

408
00:27:24,060 --> 00:27:26,060
Yes, Madam.

409
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:32,160
[Hyatt Regency]

410
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:47,400
Is it lonely to eat alone?

411
00:28:02,060 --> 00:28:03,920
Wine.

412
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:27,900
Is it delicious?

413
00:28:27,900 --> 00:28:32,000
Yes. Everything is delicious when I eat with you.

414
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:36,140
Is it delicious?

415
00:28:36,140 --> 00:28:39,420
Everything is delicious when I eat with you.

416
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:46,120
Is it lonely to eat alone?

417
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:49,600
Brother, I'm so very happy today.

418
00:29:36,340 --> 00:29:38,800
Which one do you prefer,

419
00:29:38,800 --> 00:29:43,100
going to the movies with your boyfriend or girlfriend?

420
00:29:44,020 --> 00:29:48,420
How about going to the movies with my friend?

421
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:50,860
You ruined the romantic atmosphere.

422
00:29:50,860 --> 00:29:53,660
Won't you give me a chance to pursue you again?

423
00:29:53,660 --> 00:29:56,085
No.

424
00:29:56,085 --> 00:29:59,940
Spend your time trying to pursue me with work.

425
00:29:59,940 --> 00:30:03,680
Pursuing you is happier than working hard.

426
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:08,180
I feel sorry for the employees of GU when I hear you say that.

427
00:30:08,180 --> 00:30:10,760
They have a bad vice chairman.

428
00:30:20,225 --> 00:30:24,600
Don't waste your time. Nothing's going to happen between us.

429
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:29,420
Is it because of you or because of my grandma?

430
00:30:32,540 --> 00:30:34,280
Both of them.

431
00:30:34,280 --> 00:30:38,412
Don't worry. I'm no longer a kid.

432
00:30:38,412 --> 00:30:40,720
I'll persuade my grandma.

433
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:43,720
I'm ready to give up everything for you.

434
00:30:43,720 --> 00:30:46,638
Do you want to break your grandmother's heart?

435
00:30:47,540 --> 00:30:52,720
Seriously, if you have to choose between me and your grandmother,

436
00:30:52,720 --> 00:30:55,680
will you be able to decide to choose one of us?

437
00:30:55,680 --> 00:31:00,860
What if I could choose both you and my grandma?

438
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:02,600
Is that possible?

439
00:31:02,600 --> 00:31:05,180
It must be possible, I'll make it happen.

440
00:31:05,180 --> 00:31:11,240
I'll prove to you that someone like me won't run away and give in again.

441
00:31:17,586 --> 00:31:21,100
I won't let go of you this time.

442
00:31:25,360 --> 00:31:30,533
If you don't want someone to leave, it's not enough to just hold the other person yourself.

443
00:31:30,533 --> 00:31:32,480
Both parties should hold each other.

444
00:31:32,480 --> 00:31:35,480
So you'll hold on tight and never let go.

445
00:31:39,140 --> 00:31:44,760
I'm sure I won't let it go easily.

446
00:31:44,760 --> 00:31:46,900
Trust me.

447
00:32:18,941 --> 00:32:20,214
How have you been?

448
00:32:20,214 --> 00:32:22,699
- Please sit here.
- Please.

449
00:32:22,699 --> 00:32:24,576
Sorry.

450
00:32:39,872 --> 00:32:41,620
I'll drive you home.

451
00:32:41,620 --> 00:32:44,180
It's okay. I can go back by myself.

452
00:32:44,180 --> 00:32:47,200
I brought you here. I have to send you back.

453
00:32:47,200 --> 00:32:49,500
No worries. I can go back by myself.

454
00:32:49,500 --> 00:32:50,880
You don't need to drive me.

455
00:32:50,880 --> 00:32:54,925
Thank you very much for renewing your contract with KKPP.

456
00:32:54,925 --> 00:32:57,025
That's because your products are of good quality.

457
00:32:57,025 --> 00:33:01,390
Thank you. We are happy to continue to work with you.

458
00:33:01,390 --> 00:33:06,069
We'll send you the contract for your inspection tomorrow.

459
00:33:06,069 --> 00:33:08,229
Okay. Then I'll take my leave.

460
00:33:08,229 --> 00:33:10,380
Thank you.

461
00:33:10,380 --> 00:33:12,089
Bye.

462
00:33:18,540 --> 00:33:21,178
Is it mysterious where you live?

463
00:33:21,178 --> 00:33:25,980
Every time I want to send you home, you won't let me.

464
00:33:25,980 --> 00:33:28,840
I'm not interested in any trouble at all.

465
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:32,420
What if the chairwoman's people are stalking me?

466
00:33:32,420 --> 00:33:34,671
In this case, her people will not only be watching me at work,

467
00:33:34,671 --> 00:33:37,412
but they'll be following me to my friend's apartment.

468
00:33:37,412 --> 00:33:39,557
You don't need to send me.

469
00:33:39,557 --> 00:33:42,460
Don't make me feel more depressed.

470
00:33:42,460 --> 00:33:44,980
All right.

471
00:33:44,980 --> 00:33:47,420
Text me when you get home.

472
00:33:48,466 --> 00:33:50,186
Okay.

473
00:34:01,193 --> 00:34:03,720
- Welcome next time.
- Thank you.

474
00:34:09,200 --> 00:34:11,160
Thank you.

475
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:31,500
Help me.

476
00:34:31,500 --> 00:34:37,420
Send someone to find out who Kanghan is living with. Please.

477
00:34:54,440 --> 00:34:56,540
[Worship the Buddha. Sweep away the bad luck]

478
00:34:56,540 --> 00:34:58,040
[Hope all the best]

479
00:34:58,040 --> 00:34:59,840
[Go to a movie with my girlfriend]

480
00:34:59,840 --> 00:35:01,660
"Go to a movie with my girlfriend."

481
00:35:01,660 --> 00:35:03,240
[What's going on? Hold a press conference. When will you make it public?]

482
00:35:05,600 --> 00:35:08,060
You're happy, aren't you?

483
00:35:13,505 --> 00:35:15,200
Girlfriend, right?

484
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:17,440
You're happy, aren't you?

485
00:35:21,700 --> 00:35:24,100
You're happy, aren't you?

486
00:35:30,305 --> 00:35:33,520
- Yes.
- Sorry to bother you.

487
00:35:33,520 --> 00:35:40,160
I left my phone here when I was cleaning my room this evening.

488
00:35:40,160 --> 00:35:41,978
Where did you put it?

489
00:35:41,978 --> 00:35:45,650
I think it was near the dishwasher.

490
00:35:45,650 --> 00:35:49,785
I remembered calling my daughter, and I put it there.

491
00:35:49,785 --> 00:35:51,230
Okay, I'll look for it for you.

492
00:35:51,230 --> 00:35:53,523
Okay, thank you.

493
00:36:18,273 --> 00:36:19,800
Here you are.

494
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:22,532
- Thank you, Khun Sira.
- It's okay.

495
00:36:22,532 --> 00:36:25,418
I'll take out the trash for you.

496
00:36:25,418 --> 00:36:27,209
Thank you.

497
00:36:39,299 --> 00:36:42,099
Are you going to stay up all night?

498
00:37:17,320 --> 00:37:19,200
Where's the other shoe?

499
00:37:24,179 --> 00:37:26,011
No way.

500
00:37:37,420 --> 00:37:40,020
Thank you. Stop here.

501
00:37:54,498 --> 00:37:56,519
- Nannam.
- Are you back from work just now?

502
00:37:56,519 --> 00:37:59,000
Yes, I just got back.

503
00:38:13,066 --> 00:38:17,538
I'm sorry. I didn't know, I thought you didn't want it.

504
00:38:17,543 --> 00:38:19,668
I only saw one.

505
00:38:19,668 --> 00:38:21,220
I'm sorry.

506
00:38:21,220 --> 00:38:22,660
It's all right, Madam.

507
00:38:22,660 --> 00:38:25,720
Where did you throw the garbage bag?

508
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:27,480
The garbage disposal room.

509
00:38:27,480 --> 00:38:30,080
I'll take you there.

510
00:38:34,739 --> 00:38:36,820
Khun Sira, this way.

511
00:38:36,820 --> 00:38:38,560
Okay.

512
00:38:57,472 --> 00:38:59,640
I threw your garbage bag here.

513
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:03,400
